Finisterre

The last sea,
a clear mirror,
its surface calm,
a single reflected cloud
watches the fisherman
vibrate against the tide.

The rocks echo,
their ancient forms
carved by the soft caress
of thousand tides, and moons;
the grasses rustle
a low chant,
an ocean's gentle lullaby.

— H.D.

- HD
